Since I became a member of Labour 32 years ago as a school child, provoked by the neglect of Thatcher’s government that literally collapsed my classroom, I have always advocated for better public services for those who need them most, both in my role as councillor and in my role as minister.
I have never kept my politics hidden, not even in the last election.
Everyone in Nottingham East had clarity about my policy stances and my disagreements with the current leadership.
To those who have propagated the motion on Friday, I can only say one thing: when the country moves on to a Brexit that will harm families, businesses and our public services, I do not understand the desire to waste time and energy on my loyalty to the leader of the Labour Party.
But in fact, I have only one message, and that is not addressed to Nottingham Momentum, but to my constituents, whether they are members of Labour or not: I am proud to serve you and I promise that threats to reject my candidacy as a Member of Parliament for the next elections will not affect me in your view.
